						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab set up in the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of money for feeding the Jaina ascetics, associated with the temple of Tribhuvanatilaka by <hi rend="italic">Perggaḍe</hi> Vāsiyaṇṇa's wife Chāmikabbe who was a disciple of Bāḷachandra Siddhāntadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
